{{List of coordinates}}
'''Tsumatsuhime Shrine'' is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shikiuchi shrine|1=UNKNOWN}} ({{ill|lt=Meishin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}) in {{ill|lt=Kiokuni|Q864053|WD=Q864053|1=Kii Province}}{{ill|lt=Nakusa District|Q11415547|WD=Q11415547|1=Nagusa district}}.

=== Overview ===
{{ill|lt=extension (Era name)|Q1327274|WD=Q1327274|lt=Extended|1=Enchō}} "{{ill|lt=Engishiki|Q1342448|WD=Q1342448|1=Engishiki}}" established in 5 years ({{ill|lt=927 years|Q30470|WD=Q30470|1=927}}) {{jalin k|Engishiki Shinmyocho|Q11064932|Shinmyocho}}, {{ill|lt=Kiokuni|Q864053|WD=Q864053|1=Kii Province}}{{ill|lt=Nakusa District|Q11415547|WD=Q11415547|1=Nagusa district}} "Tomatohime Shrine Meishin University The following three shrines in {{ill|lt=Wakayama Prefecture|Q131314|WD=Q131314|1=Wakayama Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Wakayama City|Q200747|WD=Q200747|1=Wakayama (city)}} are said to be {{ill|lt=Ronsha|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}} in {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917286|lt=Shikiuchi|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286|lt=Shikinaisha}} ({{ill|lt=Meishin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}), which are described as ``Monthly New Year''.
# '''{{ill|lt=#Miyakomatsuhime Shrine (Kichirei, Wakayama City)|UNKNOWN|lt=Miyakomatsuhime Shrine}}''' (Kichirei, Wakayama City) - Former {{ill|lt=Murasha|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.
# '''{{ill|lt=#Tomatohime Shrine (Hirao, Wakayama City)|UNKNOWN|lt=Tomatohime Shrine}}''' (Hirao, Wakayama City)
# '''{{ill|lt=Takazumi Shrine|Q17226307|WD=Q17226307|lt=Takazumi Shrine|1=Takatsumi Shrine}}''' (Wakayama City Negi, {{Wiki coordinates|34|14|5.04|N|135|15|41.42|E|region:JP-30_type:landmark|location|name=Takazumi Shrine}}) - It is also {{ill|lt=Ronsha|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}} of Shikinaisha ``Takazumi Hime Shrine'' and ``Takazumi Hime Shrine.'' Old village company. → See {{ill|lt=Takazumi Shrine|Q17226307|WD=Q17226307|1=Takatsumi Shrine}}.

