'''Tsumatsu Hime Shrine'' (Tsumatsu Hime Jinja, Miyako Mazu Hime Shrine) is located in {{ill|lt=Wakayama Prefecture|Q131314|WD=Q131314|1=Wakayama Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Wakayama City|Q200747|WD=Q200747|1=Wakayama (city)}}Hirao. {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=Meishin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}) {{ill|lt=Ronsha|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}}. {{Sfn|Tomatsu Hime Shrine (Shikiuchi Shrine) |1987|p=51-52}} adjacent to the ruins of Heioji Shrine on the Kumano Kodo.

=== Enshrined God ===
* {{ill|lt=Ooyatsuhime・Tsumatsuhime|Q10935047|WD=Q10935047|lt=Miyakomatsuhime no Mikoto|1=Oyatsuhime and Tsumatsuhime}}

=== History ===
{{ill|lt=Kiokuni|Q864053|WD=Q864053|1=Kii Province}}{{ill|lt=Meishin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}} "Tomatsu Hime Shrine" in {{ill|lt=Nakusa District|Q11415547|WD=Q11415547|1=Nagusa district}} {{ill|lt=Ronsha|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}}. In ``Zoku Fudoki'', there is a theory that compares the company to this, and in addition, there is a theory that compares it to ``Junior Fourth Rank Lower, Tsumatsuhiba Okami'' in the ``Kiokuni Jinmyocho'' {{Sfn|Hirao Village (Taira)|1983}}.

The company name is ``Tsumadaimyo Shrine'' in ``Zoku Fudoki,'' and ``Tsuma Gozen Shrine'' in ``Kiokuni Meisho Zue.'' According to "Zoku Fudoki", the precincts were once two and a half towns and the shrine building was majestic, but it fell into disrepair during the Tensho War, and although it was revived by {{ill|lt=Toyotomi Hidenaga|Q1191183|WD=Q1191183|1=Toyotomi Hidenaga}}, it declined. Currently, a small shrine is enshrined in the precincts of about 6 steps. Two stone lanterns dating back to {{ill|lt=Original|Q1145754|WD=Q1145754|1=Genbun}}5 ({{ill|lt=1740|Q7006|WD=Q7006|1=1740}}) stand in the shrine grounds.

Furthermore, according to "Kanei-ki", it is said that on the first day of the New Year, the first day of the Pig in October, and the first day of the New Year in November, members of the shrine of Ita-keiso Shrine once served the company.

